## When to use

- You need live answers or actions from the existing system for the goal above.
- The existing system is the source of truth and reimplementing the logic would
  risk drifting from production behavior.

## When NOT to use

- You do not have endpoint access or credentials for the live system.
- You only need static code understanding; use a read-only repo map skill.

## How to call

Each API has its own tool contract and caller script:

{% for interface in interfaces %}
```bash
{{ interface.sample_command }}
```
{% endfor %}

Every caller previews by default. It sends a request only when `--execute` is
passed and the endpoint environment variable is configured. Auth tokens are read
from environment variables and redacted in previews.

